    <h2> Our philosophy </h2>
    <p style="font-size:1.2em">Proteomics is a powerful tool to estimate the global function of a biological system. The drawback is that this amount of data typically requires dedicated tools or knowledge in programming. To assist and speed up the decision making process and demystify the data analytics process we have developed this web application. The aim is to provide researchers with a fast way to analyse data in a intuitive manner without much knowledge required in programming, statistics or the proteomics data analysis pipeline. Furthermore the power of R is leveraged to provide high quality and beautiful graphs with deep levels of user control. Finally, we have further added flexibility within ProVision to alter certain parameters for those who wish to tweak and experiment with the various parameters.</p>
    <h2> Contact us </h2>
    <p style="font-size:1.2em">ProVision is created and maintained by James Gallant. Tiaan Heunis provided code and assisted in deciding the analytical steps. The work was supported by Samantha Sampson and Wilbert Bitter. </p>
